  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".SH",
          "translatable": true
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " DESCRIPTION"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " getpid ()"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "returns the process ID (PID) of the calling process."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "(This is often used by"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "routines that generate unique temporary filenames.)"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".PP",
          "translatable": false
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " getppid ()"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "returns the process ID of the parent of the calling process."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "This will be either the ID of the process that created this process using"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " fork (),"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "or, if that process has already terminated,"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "the ID of the process to which this process has been reparented (either"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " init (1)"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "or a \"subreaper\" process defined via the"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " prctl (2)"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " PR_SET_CHILD_SUBREAPER"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "operation)."
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".SH",
          "translatable": true
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " ERRORS"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "These functions are always successful."
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".SH",
          "translatable": true
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " CONFORMING TO"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "POSIX.1-2001, POSIX.1-2008, 4.3BSD, SVr4."
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".SH",
          "translatable": true
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " NOTES"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "If the caller's parent is in a different PID namespace (see"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " pid_namespaces (7)),"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " getppid ()"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "returns 0."
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".PP",
          "translatable": false
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "From a kernel perspective,"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "the PID (which is shared by all of the threads in a multithreaded process)"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "is sometimes also known as the thread group ID (TGID)."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "This contrasts with the kernel thread ID (TID),"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "which is unique for each thread."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "For further details, see"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " gettid (2)"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "and the discussion of the"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " CLONE_THREAD"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "flag in"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " clone (2)."
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "comment",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\""
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".SS",
          "translatable": true
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " C library/kernel differences"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "From glibc version 2.3.4 up to and including version 2.24,"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "the glibc wrapper function for"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " getpid ()"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "cached PIDs,"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "with the goal of avoiding additional system calls when a process calls"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " getpid ()"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "repeatedly."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "Normally this caching was invisible,"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "but its correct operation relied on support in the wrapper functions for"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " fork (2),"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " vfork (2),"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "and"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " clone (2):"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "if an application bypassed the glibc wrappers for these system calls by using"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " syscall (2),"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "then a call to"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " getpid ()"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "in the child would return the wrong value"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "(to be precise: it would return the PID of the parent process)."
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "comment",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" The following program demonstrates this \"feature\":"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\""
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" #define _GNU_SOURCE"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" #include <sys/syscall.h>"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" #include <sys/wait.h>"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" #include <stdio.h>"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" #include <stdlib.h>"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" #include <unistd.h>"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\""
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" int"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" main(int argc, char *argv[])"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" {"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\"    /* The following statement fills the getpid() cache */"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\""
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\"    printf(\"parent PID = %ld\\n\", (long) getpid());"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\""
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\"    if (syscall(SYS_fork) == 0) {"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\"        if (getpid() != syscall(SYS_getpid))"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\"            printf(\"child getpid() mismatch: getpid()=%ld; \""
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\"                    \"syscall(SYS_getpid)=%ld\\n\","
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\"                    (long) getpid(), (long) syscall(SYS_getpid));"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\"        exit(EXIT_SUCCESS);"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\"    }"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\"    wait(NULL);"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\"}"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "In addition, there were cases where"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " getpid ()"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "could return the wrong value even when invoking"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " clone (2)"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "via the glibc wrapper function."
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "(For a discussion of one such case, see BUGS in"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " clone (2).)"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "Furthermore, the complexity of the caching code had been"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "the source of a few bugs within glibc over the years."
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "macro",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_BLOCK",
          "content": ".PP",
          "translatable": false
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "Because of the aforementioned problems,"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "since glibc version 2.25, the PID cache is removed:"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "comment",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" commit c579f48edba88380635ab98cb612030e3ed8691e"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" https://sourceware.org/glibc/wiki/Release/2.25#pid_cache_removal"
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "content",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "calls to"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "MACRO_INLINE",
          "content": ".BR",
          "translatable": false
        },
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": " getpid ()"
        }
      ],
      [
        {
          "type": "TEXT",
          "content": "always invoke the actual system call, rather than returning a cached value."
        }
      ]
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "comment",
    "lines": [
      [
        {
          "type": "COMMENT_BLOCK",
          "content": ".\\\" FIXME ."
        }
      ],
      [
